  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ Gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Cut the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> into discs, then add them to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> over a high heat and cook for 8 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside to steam dry</p><p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>pistachios</strong> to a baking tray and put in the oven for 3 min or until lightly toasted</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the<strong> lamb rump</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen</strong> <strong>paper</strong> and season all over with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once the pistachios are done, transfer them to a bowl</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned lamb</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until golden all over</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the lamb is cooking, chop the<strong> cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the tray lined with <strong>baking paper</strong>, with the <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>tomatoes</strong> with<strong> olive oil</strong>, give everything a good mix up and push them to one side of the tray – these are your <strong>balsamic tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>lamb</strong> to the other side of the tomato tray (reserve the pan for later!) and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the lamb is pink and blushing and the tomatoes have caramelised</p><p>Once the lamb is done, transfer it to a plate, cover and leave to rest for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Switch the oven off and return the balsamic tomatoes<strong> </strong>to the oven to keep warm until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2087.-step-4-x400.jpg",
